==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Safety bicycle
<hw>Safety bicycle</hw>. <def>A bicycle with equal or nearly equal
wheels, usually about 28 inches diameter, driven by pedals connected to
the rear (driving) wheel by a multiplying gear. Since the 1930's this
has been the most common type of bicycle, now simply called
<altname>bicycle</altname>. The older high-wheelers are often referred
to as <contr>bone-rattlers</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Safety chain</ent>⟦br⟧
